./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s209	Þerfor þe frene and þe þrede ydrawen  as it is seid  þan may þou chese wheþer þou will kutte it or fret it with þe þred  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s210	Iff thou will kutte it þan schalt þou take acum rostratam and putte it þur3 þe midde3 of þe lengþe of þe instrument þat is called tendiculum  bygynnyng at þe gretter ende  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s211	After take boþe þe endes of freni cesaris  drawen þur3 þe middes of þe lure and of þe hole of þe fistule  and þur3 þe middis of þe hole of þe instrument þat is called vertile  a wraiste   
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s212	Be þai drawen þur3  and be þai faste yknettid in proporcionyng þe lengþe of þe freni cesaris as it bihoueth  þat is after þe distance of þe hole of þe tendiculi to þe hole of þe fistule  þan take þe tendicule and putte þe snowte of þe nedle in þe hole of þe fistule inputtyng it strongly  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s213	Aftirward take þe wraiste wiþ freno cesaris  and put it in þe hole of þe tendicule  þat is þe side of it  whiche yputte in  putte þi fynger in þe lure  and wiþ þe toþer hand þrist faste þe tendicule with þe snowt toward þy fynger  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s214	And when þou see3 tyme  be þe wraist turned aboute þat frenum cesaris hold fast þe tendicule þat it go no3t out  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s215	And so labour þe leche vnto þat he bringe out þe poynt of þe snowte by þe middes of þe lure  and þat he streyne fast þe flesshe festned in þe frene wiþ þe wraiste and þe frene  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s216	Whiche ydo  take þe instrument þat is called coclear  a spone  Of whiche þe holow heued be putte in þe lure agayn þe poynt of þe snowte  so þat þe poynt of þe snowte stand in þe hole þat is in þe spone  no3t þur3 persed   be þat halden of þe felaw of þe leche  þis  forsoþe  shal defende þe lure þat it be no3t hurt  þru3 uncouenable mouyng and sodayn styrryng of þe pacient  wiþ þe poynt of þe rasour or of þe launcette  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s217	As soon aftirward  þe pacient comforted  putte þe leche þe poynt of þe rasour in þe holwnes of þe snowte þat is in þe spone  and  als sone as he may  boldly kutte þe flesshe festened in þe frene aboue þe snowte euen be þe middes  and it ykutte by þe middes  þe snowte wiþ þe frene shal lepe out by itself  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s219	Or if it be nede  differre it to anoþir tyme  ffor in som case þe toþer holes beyng outward may be heled wiþoute kuttyng or byndyng of þrede  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s224	But witte þou þat it is no3t required þat al þise at oone3 and togidre be putte to  but I putte þam here þat a leche  som wantyng or no3t yhad of þe forseid þingis  may competently spede wiþ þe toþer his nede3 or occupacion  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s227	And witte þou þat þe iuse of walwort or puluer of þe same  if it be had redy  is namely in euery medicyne þat is restrictiue of blode  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s230	Afterward haue he a list of wolnen cloþe  and be it bounden byhynd at þe bak of þe pacient to þe lynnen girdel  and lat it descende atuix his buttokes vpon þe cloutes couerying þe lure  and be it festned fast to þe girdel vpon þe womb  and lat it abide so stille to þe tyme come þat it be eftsones remoued  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s231	If þe holes  forsoþe  be in þe buttok somdele remoued fro þe lure  þan most it oþerwise be bounden  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s232	And þat þus  haue þe pacient a wolnen girdel or a lynnen  wiþ þe whiche he be girded in þe flanke3  to þe whiche girdel be hongen a lynnen cloute hauyng in brede seuen or ynches  and in lengþe als many or mo  þerfore be þe pacient girded þat þe side of þe clout next to þe lure lye ri3t atuix þe buttokkes upon þe lure  and oþir cloutes yputte atuix  þan be bounden two listis hyngyng about þe þie of þe pacient  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s233	And if boþe þe buttokkes bene hurt  ordeyne he anoper girdel to þe toþer  and be it ordeyned as it is seid afore  and on þe same wise  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s236	fforsoþe when þou seest  in þe secound day or þe þrid  þe blode wele staunched  þan take þe 3olke of a raw ey  and wiþ oile roset or of camomille  or wiþ sanguis veneris  or  þise defailyng  distempre it wiþ comon oile  and put it in a littel bleddre  and wiþ anastar of tree ich day but oones be it 3etted into þe lure  so þat þe wounde be filled þerof

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s271	And inalsmych as þai ar more drye insomych þai ar þe better

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s276	Or for oþer notable cause3 being þer  þan may þe lech with kuttyng of þe þrede ydrawen thur3 þe midde3 of þe hole of þe fistule and þe lure kutte þe flesch  and þat availeþ even to kuttyng with iren  outtake þat it askeþ a longer tyme of curyng  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s277	For why  þofal it be bounden ri3t streitly at þe first tyme 3itte vnneþe schal þe fretyng be complete in som men by a moneþ or thre weke3  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s278	Sich cure þerfor ysewed and þe festnyng ydo on dewe maner  þat is after þat þe pacient may resonably suffre  puruey þe leche if þe pacient be delicate or feble  or waike of hert  þat þe þrede by which þe fistule is knytte  be so bonden þat if it be nede þat it may be loused without kuttyng  þat is with a lache knotte or slyppyng knotte

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s282	Witte þou þat þus ow þou to chaufe þe 3olk of an ey with oyle

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s284	Þan afore þe pacient go to þe priuè  take þe leche þe forseid þrede in þe lure  and be þe vtter knotte loused  and aftir be þe þrede more strongly constreyned if it may wiþout anguissh of þe pacient  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s285	Elle3  forsoþe  be it bounden wiþ tuo knottis or þre vnlouseable  and be þe heuede3 of þe þrede3 kutte away so nere þe knotte þat þai may no3t be perceyued of þe pacient or of oþer men

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s295	If al  forsoþe  may not be hadde  take þe toþer þat þou may haue  and namely þe þre first named wiþ wodebynd if þou may haue it  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s298	Aftir be þer put to þam of subtile mele of whete als moche as sufficeþ  and medle þam wele togidre  þan putte to a litle oyle of olyue  or of fressh buttre scomed at þe fire  wiþ als miche virgine wax togidre dissolued at þe fire by it self  þan first putte aboue þe iuse to þe fire wiþ hony and white of eyren  and mouse þam all wayse wiþ a sklyse þat þai cleue not to þe panne  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s299	When forsoþe it is wele hote but not wele ysoþen  be þe wax molten wiþ oile or buttre  as it is seyde aboue  whiche ymolten and þe forseid þingis beyng hote  þat is to seye þe hony  þe iuse  and þe white of eyren  be þai 3etted togidre  and so euermore mouyng strongly wiþ a spatour  seþe þam on a softe fyre vnto þey be made oon body  whiche ydo  sette it of þe fire  and it beyng hote  putte to of terebentyne als moche as sufficeþ and moue it strongly wiþ a spature vnto þat þe terebentyne be dronken in  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s305	And it eseþ wele þe akyngis and þe bolnyngis of ioyntures  þis  forsoþe  haue I ful ofte proued

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s316	Or  if he may  þat is better þat þey be kutte al fro oon hole to anoþer  acu rostrata  þe snowted nedle yputte in þe hole  or som lynne tent  kutte þam to þe grounde wiþ a rasour or wiþ a launcete  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s320	Of þe kuttyng  forsoþe  of longaon  blode went strongly out  for þe fistule was ri3t depe  wherefore þe pacient swowned  þerfore I putte to a sponge wette in cold watir and receyued þe blode  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s326	And witte þou þat I saw neuer man vnder my hand suffre swounyng  outake hym þis  he was forsoþe corpulent and waike of hert  but neþerlesse aboute þe fourty day after þe kuttyng he rode  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s327	I heled anoþer man þat had a fistule in þe same maner in all þingis  outake þat longaon  was no3t persed  whom I cured wiþ kuttyng in þe same maner as it is seid of þe first  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s328	I haue sene som men hauyng oon hole aloon ni3 þe lure þat persed no3t þe longaon  whom I heled wiþ puluer sine pari finaly  but for þe mouþe of þe vlcere was ouer streit  first I put aboue of vnguento ruptorio of calce viue  sape for to large þe mouþe of the fistule  of whiche it shal be treted afterward among oþir confeccions  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s329	I haue sene som men haue tuo holes byside þe lure  of whiche oon persed þe longaon and þe toþer persed in no place  but it was oonly symple by itself in þe flesshe  hauyng no passyng to þe tother hole  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s330	Of whiche was such a cure   The hole nerre þe lure was cured wiþ kuttyng or byndyng  þe toþer  forsoþe  wiþ poudre sine pare yput in and diaflosmo  and oon emplastre þat is called Neyrbone put aboue  whos confeccion shal be shewed aftirwarde  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s331	I saw also  and  oure lord beyng mene  I heled perfitely a man þat had ffistula in ano on þe ri3t side and on þe lefte side  whiche  forsoþe  had on þe lefte buttok hole3  and þre in þe ri3t buttok  and wiþin was longaon persed toward þe ri3t side oonly  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s332	But neþerlesse all þe holes of aiþer party of þe lure answered togidre in þe grounde þat was proued þus  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s333	I toke a siryng of siluer and a bleddre ybounden aboute ful of sanguis veneris  and þe siryng yputte in þur3 oon hole and þe bleddre compressed wiþ þe fyngers  þe oile in3etted went out by al þe holes togidre on boþe sides  and neþerlesse þe hole of longaon answered no3t but to oon hole oonly  and þat in þe ri3t buttok  þe soþefastnes of whiche þing was proued wiþ þe instrument þat is callid sequere me  and wiþ acu rostrata  wiþ ful gret hardnes and bisynes  þe cure of whiche was suche  ffirst euery day in þe lefte buttok þur3 oon of þe holes I 3etted in sanguis veneris wiþ þe forseid siring and bledder  whiche ydo  I putte in tuo tentes or þre  or lard of pork or swyne in þe larger holes  after þat þe depnes of þe fistules asked  þe heuedes  forsoþe  of þe tentes war tokned with þredes drawen þur3 þe middes wiþ a nedell  þat þe tentes shuld no3t be drowned in þe grounde of þe fistules when þe tentes war put in  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s335	I lefte it in pece vnto þe morne  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s336	At morne  forsoþe  þe emplastre remoued  þer appered aboue 3e emplastre ful putrid quitour in superflue quantite  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s340	Euermore continuyng þe cure wiþ þe siryng in þe lefte side  and wiþ tentes als long as þay wolde entre in  and þe emplastre Neyrbon yputte aboue  and salus populi and vnguento Arabico  vnto a loueable ende wiþ goddes help aboute half a 3ere I cured hym  and lefte hym in pece  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/arderne_fistula_converted.xml	s341	Also þer bene som men þat haþ fistules no3t apperyng outward  but þay putte out miche putred  watrye humour  and somtyme clere blode  and somtyme blode ymedled wiþ quitour

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_anatomy_interpolated_converted.xml	s313	And þes bones be cleped vernalia be cause of her commissure  þat is cleped vernalis  when it is ioyned wiþ þe commissure þat is cleped coronalis  þe vtilite whi þat þe bones of þe braine panne ben togider  so as it were a sawe   none oþere of alle þe bodie  is be cause þat it is nescessaire þat mo þinges passe þoru3 þe commissures of þe heued þen bi enye oþere commissures

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_anatomy_interpolated_converted.xml	s319	þe ferþe skille is be cause þat þe substaunce of þe braine is wunder nere to þe holes of þe Eres and þo bones vernalia ben þer febel  þerfore  be cause of more alteracioun of Eire  þo bones þat ben cleped petrosa ben addedto in þat place þat þe eire þat passeþ þur3 hem to þe braine mowe ben degraded in manye maners  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_anatomy_interpolated_converted.xml	s320	þe vtilite of þe same bones þat ben cleped petrosa bi maner off appodiacioun oþer leninge and whi þat þe iunctures of hem be serratil oþere liche to a sawe  but superficiel allonelie  forwhi  3if þei holed þur3 þe bones þat ben cleped vernalia  þei schulde raþer make hem more febel þen conforten hem

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_anatomy_interpolated_converted.xml	s323	þe secounde cause oþer profite is for þat sownes oþer noises þat ben excellent  horribel schulde not passen sodeinlie and euen to þe braine and hurte him  for excelent sensibilite corupteþ þe witte  but be cause of longe dwellinge in þe forseid reuoluciouns his excellens is made lesse

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s57	Þai beeþ clepid lymes and instrumentis  for þai beeþ þe instrumentis of þe soule  as þe hand  þe face  þe herte  the lyuer

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s64	And þogh þe forsaide instrumental membres beþ compownede of many þinges by grace of þe dede and of suffrynge of hem with dewe quantite and qualite in al manere makynge  neuerþelatter oo manere symple makynge and like among hem is þe bygynnynge of al þe dede  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s65	Þe oþer forsoþe beþ by grace of a manere profitablenesse  some þat þe actes beþ made þe bettre  and oþer wiþoute þe whiche it was not possible hym to be made  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s66	Oþer forsoþe beeþ made for þe kepyng of alle þise  as þise beeþ ladde into þe hondes in þe firste and in þe secounde book of Profite of Particles and so by consequent in þe folowynge bokes is in alle oþer membres  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s67	So þat þou schalt vnderstonde  as he saiþ in þe fourþe book  after þe beste no body to be ydel ne vayne  but to be made after þe nede wiþ convenient complexioun and makynge and some good vertues 3euen of þe creatoure or makere  þe whiche manere vertues beþ take by lotte in compowned membres and in symple  as in symple membres of þe elementes

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s297	Þere beeþ also bones of þe neyþer iowe  of þe whiche Galien saith in xi=o= capitulo penultimo  Of þe lowest parties forsoþe of the cheke a bone haþ only in itself oo dyuisioun  noght alwaie ischewed after þe vttermeste of þe berde  þat he saiþ is made for dyndymacioun  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s298	And he haþ in þe extremytees a 3okkynge togedre iputte to al aboute toward þe muscle of þe temples  thenontes and verbyformes icleped openynges  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s299	Folwyngliche it is to come to þe particles of þe mowthe  þe whiche beeþ  þe lippes  of þe whiche it is saide   þe tieþ  the tonge  þe palate and þe vuule  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s300	The tieþ forsoþe beeþ of þe kynde of bones  þogh þai be saide to haue felynge  after Galien in =o= De Vtilitate  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s301	Neuerþelatter þat is by resoun of some synowes goynge downe fro þe þridde payre to þe roote of ham  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s302	Þay beeþ at þe moste 3=ti=  þat is to say in eyþer iowe  þogh þat in some men is nou3t ifounde but   þat is to say  þe euene tieþ and fourcornerde and tuskes  grynderes and caysales  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s307	He haþ forsoþe muscles  the whiche spryngen of þe arwely addicioun and fro þe bone vnder þe tonge

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s310	Byhynde þe tonge toward þe palate beþ þe chekes and wales and þe hyngynge vuule  to make redy þe ayre to here helpynge  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s311	The palate forsoþe is cleped al þe ouer parte of þe mowþe  and it is folden wiþ his parties in a manere pannycle of þe stomak and of þe wesaunte  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s312	And be þise inow of þe parties of þe face  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s316	There beth forsoþe in þe nekke double parties  conteynynges  þe whiche kepen propreliche þe nekke  and conteyned  þe whiche passen by hit  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s317	Þe conteynynge parties beþ þe skyn  flesshes  muscles  ligamentes and bones  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s318	The conteynede beeþ icleped þe trache  cleped þe wesaunte or þe mowthe of þe stomak or mery  or þe þrote  of synowes  veynes and arteries and a partie of þe nuke or of þe mary of þe bakke  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s320	Þe anothomye ispedde and þe þrote or þe nekke departed byfore after þe lengþe  first schal appere þe trache  i þe þroteful arterie   þe whiche is þe way of þe ayre to þe longe  passynge fro it to þe þrote or to þe wesaunt  made of many grustly rynges not fulfilled  ioyned to þe mouth of þe stomak  ifastned and bounden wiþ a strong pannycle and li3t  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s321	Þan byhynde þat  aboue þe spondyles  is ysophagus  i þe wesaunt   þe whiche is þe way of þe mete goynge fro þe þrote  persynge þe mydrede vnto þe wombe or þe stomak  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s323	Aboue þise two wayes fro þe party of þe mowthe is gula  epiglotoun  or þe þrote  þat I acounte al for oon of þis tyme  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s324	And it is a ful grustly particle  made to be þe instrument of þe voyce and þe keye of þe þrote in þe tyme of swolowynge  medlynge a manere addicioun schape like a tonge  þe whiche is in oon of his partyes  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s326	Than þou schalt considre double synowes  descendynge to þe stomak and to þe bowels  croked a3eyne for þe felynge and turnynge a3en to wiþynne aboue next þe þroote  for þe voyce  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s327	Also þow schalt considre þe grete veynes and arteryes þe whiche gone vpward  ibraunched nygh þe furcle  by þe sides of þe nekke to þe ouer parties  þe whiche beþ cleped þe depe guidege and appopletice or subetales  þe kyttynge of þe whiche is ful perilouse  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s328	Folwyngliche by grace of þe conteynynge parties and makynge þe nekke  þe whiche beeþ þe skynne  fleisshes  muscles  ligamentis and bones or lynkes or ioyntes  by þe general anothomye iseyne of þe rygge bones and of al þe bakke  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s331	Galien saiþ  =o= et 3=o= De Vtilitate Particularum  þat in þe bak beþ grete partes  þat is to saye  þe nekke  þe spawdes  þe lendes  and it is icleped of some men þe holy bone and of some men þe large bone  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s332	After þe nekke þere beeþ spondiles or lynkes  and after þe spawdes  and after þe lende  and after þe holy bone  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s333	Þere beeþ þerfore verrey spondiles and of þe holy bone and þre of þe tayle bone  þe whiche forsoþe beþ nou3t spondyles but like to ham as vikaries  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s334	For the firste þre beeþ ful grete  and þay haue noþer echynges ne holes in þe sides but tofore  and þai beeþ ful grustly  and nameliche þe laste  makyng hamself smalle to þe manere of a tayle  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s335	And so at þe moste þere beeþ 3=ti= spondiles or lynkes  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s336	And if a payre of synowe spryngynge fro þe nuke  i þe mary of þe bak bone  passe by eueriche spondyle  þere schal be 3=ti= of synowes of þe nuke and oo synowe wiþoute felawe  þat spryngeþ of þe laste partie þerof  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s337	And if þere springe of þe brayne  þe summe of synowes schal be 3=ti=  as it was seide aboue of synowes of þe hede and of þe kynde of þe nuke  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s338	Ther beþ also ouer þat some brawny flesshes liggynge after þe lengþe of þe forsaide bak in þe sides of þe spondyles as þay were a matresse to þe synowes  þe whiche beeþ icleped þe loynes  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s339	And þerwiþ is a pannycle bynding all þe bak bones as is aboue þe brayne panne and oþer grete bones  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s340	Ther beþ þerfore in þe nekke spondyles by whos sides ipersed passen out payre of synowes fro þe parte of þe nuke þe whiche passeþ þere  þe whiche beren felynge and movyng to þe schuldres and to þe armes and to some parties of þe hede and of þe same nekke  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s341	The flesshes of þe nekke beþ þrefolde  þat beeþ propurliche icleped þe longe hatrelles liggynge  as it is isayde  full brawny nygh þe spondiles  of þe whiche þe tenauntes beþ made þat moven the heed and þe nekke  þe whiche beeþ =ti= in noumbre  as Galien saiþ   and flesshes fulfillynge þe voyde places  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s342	The comune ligamentes byndynge þe heed wiþ þe nekke and wiþ þe spawdes beþ manye  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s343	In þe former partie beþ two grete ligamentes discendynge from vnder þe eeres to þe furcle  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s344	In þe hyndermore partie forsoþe beeþ oþer more ligamentis byndynge þe spondiles of þe bak  goyng downe in þe sides to þe spawdes and oþer moste membres  so þat þe muscles  þe tenouns and þe ligamentis stonden in þe circuite or compasse of þe nekke  makynge a rowndeness  bowyng and liftyng vp and wrappynge aboute þe nekke and þe hede  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s349	And alle þoo beeþ perilouse  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s350	It semeþ also þat kyttinges in it schal be made after þe lengþe  for soche is þe goynge of his parties  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s353	AFter þe nekke folweþ þe ovene or þe brest bone  but for þat the schuldres beeþ isette aboue þe ouer parties þerof  and by consequent þe armes  þerfore of ham firste it is to be saide  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s354	Þe schulder blade  þe spawde and þe schuldre  be þis itaken al for oon in þis present  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s356	Þise þinges forsoþe beeþ to þe makynge and defendynge of þe holwe membres  in primo De Vtilitate per totum  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s358	Aristotel forsoþe saide wel  for he saide þe hond bifore þe holow membres and resoun bifore craftes  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s361	The muscles and þe coordes movyng þe arme  descendynge fro þe nekke and þe breste  passen by it  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s362	And þai  takyng and wrappynge þe ioyntour of þe elbowe or þe helpyng bone  be inplanted  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s363	The synowes beeþ drawe oute of þe marye of þe nekke  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s365	And  for soche in þe schuldres beþ nou3t mykel schewed  of ham þe speche is made schort  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s366	Of bones it is to wite þat þai bene two  þe firste is þe schulder bone of þe partie of þe bak  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s367	The secounde bone is þe furcle on þe breste half  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s370	The firste is þe pitte  þe whiche is in þe myddes  resceyuynge þe hede of the elbowe  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s375	And it byndeþ and fastneþ þe two croked echynges þat þe pitty echynge in þe myddel holde þe more stably þe hede of þe elbowe in þe ioynte  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s376	Tho echynges forsoþe beþ none oþer bones fro þe schulder bone  as Lamfranque and Henry sayen  but þai beeþ substancial parties þerof  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s377	And experience techeþ þat þis is trewe  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s378	And so affermeþ Galien 3=o= De Vtilitate Particularum  capitulo =o= et =o=  sayenge þat þe schulder blades by plente of extremytees helleþ þe schulder and fastnynge it priuely  togidre it schulde be forsoþe þe hillynge and þe kepyng of al the articulacioun  i couplynge togedre  after þe schuldre  togedre forsoþe and to forbyd þe hede of þe arme to passe oute aboue  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s379	And þerwiþal it haþ þre grete fastenynge goyng out of þe hede of þe schuldre to þe elbowe  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s380	And in þe circuyte it is streyned wiþ the moste tenouns sprongen fro þe moste muscles  i brawnes   comynge fro þe breste and fro þe schuldre  isette in þe bone of þe elbowe  mouynge hym  some forsoþe goyng vpward  some dounward  and some turne ham rounde aboute  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s381	The partie forsoþe vnder þe forsaide ioynte is icleped þe arme hole  þe whiche is fulfilled wiþ glandulouse flesche  in þe whiche is assigned þe purgynge places of þe herte  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s382	Folowyngly it is to saye of þe arme  þat is icleped þe grete hand  the whiche Galien  in =o= De Vtilitate  capitulo =o=  dyuydeþ into þre grete partes  one forsoþe is þe elbowe  anoþer forsoþe is þe litel arme  and anoþer forsoþe is cleped attrachita  i þe litel hond   
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s384	Of þe schewed arteries and veynes þe whiche beeþ founden in þe armes  a speche is imade togedre for þe cause aforseide  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s385	After forsoþe þat þay comen fro here principles in braunchynge to þe arme holes  þai beeþ ibraunched þere in two parties  whereof oo partie spredeþ to þe vtter partie of the arme and þat oþer to þe furþer partie  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s387	And oo braunche goþ vpward byhynde þe schuldre to þe hede  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s388	And þat oþer in goyng downe is braunched in tweyne  wherof oon is dyuyded by þe arme wiþoute in many parties  and it is icleped þe ende of þe arme  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s390	And þerof it descendiþ to þe hand  and it is schewed bytwene þe þombe and þe schewynge fyngre  and it is cleped þe eye veyne  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s391	That parte forsoþe whiche was departed in þe arme holes þat spredeþ to the ynner partie in descendynge  it is schewed in þe bou3te of þe arme  and it is cleped basilica  i þe base veyne   
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s393	Fro þise two forsaide veynes when þay beeþ in þe boghte of þe arme  a comune braunche is braunched þe whiche appereþ in þe myddel of boþe  þe whiche is cleped mediana  þe myddel veyne or þe bodely  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s395	Þere beeþ forsoþe many oþer braunches of þe whiche a cirurgien haþ nou3t to considre for þaire litelnesse  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s396	Of synowes it is saide þat notable synowes comen downe fro þe nuke by þe lynkes of þe nekke to eyþer arme  one byhynde  anoþer bifore  one aboue  anoþer byneþe  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s398	Muscles  i brawnes  beþ made of þe forsaide synowes  of flesche and of pannycles  þat is to say  þe principal and grete muscles in þe adiutorie  i aboute þe boghte of þe arme  movynge þe litel arme  and þerynne movynge the litel hande  and in þe hond movynge þe fyngresWhos synowy cordes beþ so imade open  as it is saide aboue  and þay beþ made naked fro flesshe by fynger brede nygh þe ioynte  and if þai be wounded þai brynge yn greet perile  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s399	There beeþ also in þe arme many ligamentis  þe whiche descenden fro þe bones and passen by ioyntes  and þai holden ham bounden wiþ cordes imade large  whos kyttynge is ful harmeful  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s401	In þe firste partie  þe whiche is cleped þe vlne or þe adiutorie  i þe cubite   is a bone ful of marye and rounde at eyþer ende  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s402	And þe ouer roundenesse  þe whiche is one alone  entreþ into a box or a pytte of þe schuldre  and it makeþ þe schulder ioynte  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s404	And in þe ynner partie it haþ a manere litel semynge or struttynge  and byhynde it haþ a manere of holownesse  in þe whiche þe heed or þe croked echynge of þe more focyle is resceyued in þe tyme of raxynge of þe arme  so þat þo roundenessis entren into þe holownesses of þe fociles  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s406	And þay maken the ioynte in þe myddel of þe arme in þe whiche þe litel arme bygynneþ  þe whiche is þe secounde parte aforesaide  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s407	In þe whiche beeþ two bones icleped þe fociles  þat is to say  þe more  þe whiche is wiþyn  the whiche is saide to be lenger þan þat oþer for þe hoked echynge  and goþ toward þe litel fyngre  in makynge wiþouteforth a bougy semynge in þe manere of a pynne  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s408	Þe lesse forsoþe is aboue  and it gooþ fro þe boghte of þe arme vnto þe honde toward þe þombe as þogh he wolde eche in it  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s409	And in eyþer hede of ham beþ pittes resceyuynge þe rowndenesses

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chauliac_cyrurgie_converted.xml	s411	And þay beeþ boþe gretter and ioynynge ham in þe ioynte  and þay beþ smaller in þe myddel  and þe more atwene  þat þay schulde holde þe synowes and muscles

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s226	And þis pannycle is ma=a=d principaly for two causis  of þe whiche þe firste is þis  þat he by his strong byndinge togidere schulde make ferme  sad þe feble coniunccioun of þe bonys of þe heed  The secunde is þis  þa=t= it schulde be putt bitwene þe nei3sche lacertis of þe heed  and þe hard braynpanne  so þat it schulde be a mene  þat þe harde schulde not touche  hurt  þe neische   And þus endiþ þe firste doctrine of þis chapitre But neuerþelattere in þe þridde doctrine of þis same chapitre schal be told in partie of þe pannycles þat beþ vndir þe scolle  closinge þe brayn  The secunde doctrine of þis chapitre schal treten of þe secunde principal partie of þe heed  þat is to seie þe scolle  her parties  þe which is compouned of dyuers bonys  hauynge certeyne semes hackid eiþir in oþir  as it were oon sawe in anoþir   it is hard  pleyne boþe wiþinne  wiþoute  spoungious in þe myddil  and also in his schap in partie round   sumdel euelong  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s227	But whi and wherfore  God and kynde þat noþing doiþ wi=t=houte cause  haþ ordeyned þe scolle of þe heed  for to be maad in sich a maner as I haue rehersid aforn  it schal be declarid hereaftirward  euene bi þe same ordre as it is abouenrehersid  ffirst  whi þe scolle was ma=a=d of manye diuers bonys  þer ben two comoun causis  of whiche þe firste is þis  for þe commoditees  þe profitis  þat longen to þe selue scolleboon  The secunde is taken for þe commoditees  profitis þa=t= beþ conteyned vndir   wiþinne þe same scolle  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s228	So þanne þou schalt vndirstonden  þat þe firste of þe causis conteyneþ in himsilf þre vtilitees  of whiche þe firste is þis  If it hadde be so  þat þe scolle hadde ben al oon boon  whanne it hadde suffrid heuy hurt  or greuaunce in his oon partie  þanne it schulde haue greued al þe hool scolle   þerfore it was compowned    The ij vtilite is þis  for it is greet nede þat þe braynpanne be in o place hard   in anoþir part neische   if it hadde be so  also were al oon boon  þanne whanne þe harde part hadde ony smytynge  þe neische part schulde be hurt greuously þou3 þe harde part hadde noon harme  The þridde vtilite is þis  þat if þe scolle hadde be al oon boon  it my3te happe sumtyme  þat bi oon strok it schulde haue ij hurtis  as if it were hurt in þe hard part  woundid  þe neische part my3te also be folden togidere   be more greuous þan þat oþir   So þanne to þese two causis as to þe partis  þat beþ conteyned vndir   wiþinne þe scolleboon  þer beþ approprid vtilitees  The firste is þis  þa=t= þe veynes whiche þat bryngiþ norischinge vnto þe brayn moun sutilly entren yn bi þe ioyncturis of þe parties of þe heed  and if þe scolle had be o contynued boon vndepartid  þei my3ten not haue entrid so    The secunde is  þat þe senewis sensible  motif mowen go out by hise semes   berynge felynge and meuynge to oþere partis of þe heed  The þridde  þat þe fumositees þat arn arerid vp  from þe brayn  mowen passe out bi þe aforseid seemes  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s229	 The fourþe  þat þe dura mater my3te be hongid vp bi þe serratilis of þe diuers partis of þe scolle  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s230	 fforþermore  whi þe seemes of þe scolle arn serratyk  it is for þis cause  ffor it is ri3t necessarie þat þe senewis  veynes  þe fumositees schulden passe out bi þilke open semes  whiche þingis hadde be vnpossible  if þei hadden not be maad in sich a maner    But whi þat þe Braynpanne is hard  it is pr=i=ncipaly for þis cause  for þat it schulde defende þe bettere þe brayn and þe pannyclis from harmes  noyauncis wiþoutforþ    Whi þat it is playn wiþouten  þat is  for it schulde not hurte þe pannyclis  þat bynden þe bonys wiþoutforþ  And whi þat it is playn wiþinne  þat is for it schulde not hurte dura mater wiþinneforþ  fforþermore  whi it is spongeous in þe myddil  þer beþ assigned þre causis  The firste  þa=t= þe fumositees of þe brayn  my3te þe bettere passe out bi þe porrosite  The secunde  þat it schulde be þe more li3t  lest þat þe brayn schulde be agreued þoru3 his heuynes  The is  þat bi his porrosite  þe blood þat is norischinge to þe brayn  schulde be þe bettere kept  But whi it is round  þer beþ assigned two causis  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s231	The firste  for it my3te conteyne þe mo þingis  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s232	ffor a round figure is of a grettere capacite  þan arn oþere figuris  As Galien witnessiþ in þe =o= de luuamentis in þe ende of þe chapitre  where he puttiþ þe vtilitees of round figuris  The secunde  þat it kepe þe bettere boþe him  þe brayn from noyauncis and harmes wiþoutforþ  And also whi it is sumdel euelong  þer beþ putt two causis  The firste is  for þe substaunce of þe brayn  lijþ sumdel eelong   þerfore þe bonys weren ordeyned  of þe same schap  The ij þat þe senewis  þe Nucha þat springen from þe firste   þridde ventricle of þe brayn  schulden haue space to goon out bitwixe þe brayn and þe scolle  lest so by her outgoynge  þei comen a3en þe braynpanne wiþouten mene  hadde ony hurtynge   The noumbre of þe bonys of þe heedscolle is seid diuers  of diuers men by diuers consideracioun

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s263	ffor truly I foond in þe Charnel of seynt marie spetil at londoun  a scolleboon þa=t= was al oon hool boon lijk a basenett  outaken oonliche þe ij smale petrouse bonys  þe neþir chekeboon   And þus endiþ þe secunde doctr=i=ne of þis chapitre  The þridde doctr=i=ne of þis chapitre schal treten of þe pr=i=ncipal partie  entrynge þe composicioun of þe vppere partie of þe heed  where þou schalt vndirstonden  þat þis partie is pr=i=ncipaliche of þingis  þat is to witen  Of pannyclis  Of Brawnys   of his emoynctorijs  fro whos composicioun comeþ veynes to þe lyuere  passynge þoru3 þe hole of Tanda  and so sprediþ forþ þoru3 al carnosite of þe heed bi þe serratile semes  and so þei goon doun byneþe þe braynpanne  and þere þei meten wiþ þe arteries comynge fro þe herte  þe whiche whanne þei ben knytt togidere  þei maken þe dura mater  and sche is hangid vp bi þe serratil semes of þe scolle  wiþ veynes  senewis and arteries  þe whiche þre goon out bi þe same semes  and wiþouten þe brayn panne  þei maken a pannycle þat byndiþ and halt togidere alle þe bonys of þe heed  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s266	The secunde is þis  þat quytture  corrupcioun þat comeþ of a wounde þat oþirwhile happiþ to be ma=a=d in þe heed  schulde by hir be kepid and be holden vp  þat it nei3e not þe dura mater ne þe brayn  So þanne vndir þis pannicle  lijþ anoþir pannycle þat is more neische  more tendir þan þis  which þa=t= is clepid pia mater  and þis pannycle is in summe placis departid from þe brayn  and in summe placis he is contynued wiþ þe Brayn by veynes and arteries  þe whiche goon out of him  entren into þe diuisiouns of þe brayn  and drinken yn of þe braynes substaunce  makynge alyue   3euynge to him þe spirit of lijf  for þe kynde of þe brayn is departid  chaungid aftir þat it bifalliþ to þe vertues of þe animal werkis  The cause whi þer beþ mo pannyclis in þe brayn þan oon  is þis  ffor if þere were but oon pannycle  ouþir yt muste be hard  or it muste be neische  or ellis it muste be meene  but if it were so þat it were hard  þanne yt schulde hurte þe brayn  and if it were neische  þan it schulde be hurt of þe braynpanne  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s267	But if it were mene bitwene hardnesse  neischenes  þanne it schulde boþe hurte and be hurt  as it is seid aforn  And þerfore god and kynde  han ordeyned  þat þer ben tweyne  þat is to seie  þat oon hard and þat oþir neische  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s268	The harde  þat it my3te be a mene bitwene þe scolle   þe pia mater  and þe neische  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s269	And þe neische  þa=t= it my3te be a meene bitwene þe harde and þe brayn  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s270	So here þou schalt vndirstonde  þat aftir þe aforseid veynes and arteries han yma=a=d þe pia mater  and sett here togidere  þanne þei entren þe subiect of þe brayn  askynge to hem of þe herte lijf and breeþ  and of þe lyuere norischinge  But soþely  þis spirit or breeþ in the salue brayn is defied by a forþere digestioun   so be made þere þe lyue of a beest  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s271	Pia mater wiþouten mene touchiþ þe brayn and deuidiþ apertly þe forseid spirit into þre ventriclis of þe brayn  þe which diuisioun apperiþ more in þe firste ventricle  þan in þe oþere ij  insomiche þat þei ben seid to be iiij ventriclis of þe brayn  In þe firste partie of þe firste ventricle of þe brayn is ordeyned vertu  þe which is clepid comoun witt  or fantasie  and he takiþ alle þe formes or ordynauncis þat ben disposid of þe fyve wittis  aftir þe remocioun or meuynge of sensible þingis  In þe secunde partie of þe firste ventricle  is ordeyned or founden ymagynatif vertu  þe whiche resseyueþ of þe comoun witt  þe spicis and þe foormes of sensible þingis  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s272	as þei weren taken of þe comoun witt wiþoutenforþ  representynge þere owne schap  ordynauncis  vnto þe memoratif vertu þat folowiþ hereaftirward    But soþely al þe brayn as it schal be seid hereaftirward  is diuidid to be cold and moist  Neþeles þis ventricle ys seid to be hoot and drie  hauynge reward to þe oþere two ventriclis  The secunde ventricle or þe myddil is myche lasse þan þe oþere ventriclis  in þe which is founden þe estymatyf vertu  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s273	And þere he rehersiþ  schewiþ   declariþ   demeþ  þo þingis þat ben offrid to him bi þat oþir ventricle  as y seide aforn  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s275	 In þe þridde ventricle is founden or ordeyned þe memoratif vertu  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s276	And þis ventricle is more þan þe secunde  and lasse þan þe firste  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s277	But in comparacioun to þe oþere  it is demed hoot and drie  þe which resseyueþ þe þingis þat ben schewid and þeir sentencis  and kepiþ hem in tresour  or ellis puttiþ hem forþ  aftir þe discrecioun of þe v wittis  vnto þe organs or þe instrumentis of animal werkis  out of whos extremitees springiþ þe Nucha  by þe hoole of þe boon landa or Basillare  as it is seid aforn  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s278	And þese parties ben callid ventriclis byasmyche as euery partie of hem  haþ a foorme as of a wombe wiþ a maner of roundnesse  and also þei beþ holow3  for ellis þei my3ten not resseyuen in hem þe spiritis of lijf  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s288	 But two causis þer ben  whi þer ben in þe heed mo ventriclis þan oon  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s289	 The firste is þis  for þat þe spiritis schulden dwellen by sufficient tyme to þe laste digestioun  The secunde  for ech of hem schulde sufficiently haunten and worchen hise owne werkis  vpon þingis ytaken or vndirfongen  or þei passiden from oon ventricle to anoþir  Of þe þridde part  þa=t= is of þe emunctorijs  Galien telliþ  libro de iuuamentis in þe firste  in þe secunde chapitres  þat vndir þe brayn  bitwene þe dura mater   þe boon þa=t= is foundement of þe brayn  þere beþ tweyne neþere emunctorijs of þe brayn  þat ben ysprungen of þe pia mater  and he is seid  Lacirria  wiþ whom ben conteyned þe two canellis and the ventricle of þe brayn   he is round  large and open abouen  and streyt bineþen til he entre þe heed of the Glandule  and also he is holow3   ykeuerid wiþ a wondirful nett  the which strecchiþ him sumwhat fro þe Glandula  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s290	And þou schalt vndirstonden þat þese two eminctorijs beþ þe beste kept lymes þat beþ in al þe body  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/chirurgie_de_1392_converted.xml	s291	ffor a man schulde raþere dien þan ony of þese two emunctorijs schulden suffren ony nocumentis wiþoutenforþ    And þus endi=t=h þe þridde doctrine  and þe laste of þis chapitre  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/cophon_experimentes_converted.xml	s1	Liber Cophonis Here bygynnen þe Exprimentes of Cophon þe leche of Salerne For ache of heued þat comeþ of fleumatyk betokeneþ þe nose ystoppyd and þe eyen watery and heuy of slepe and þe mouþe moist For þis maladie do 3if þe seek jeralogodion 3if he may vse and 3if he may no3t 3if hym wyne laxatiue Or elles tak setwort polipodie auence and crowlek and percily bysshopwort and mastic and seþe alle þes in water and do hony to and 3if þis ache falle to þe gomes do enoynt wiþ marciaton or wiþ aragon ate fure and þan do þe seek go to slepe bote engorge ate þe bygynnyng þe licour beforsayd and 3if þat it comeþ a doune and freteþ þe gomes tak þe pouder of þe bark of þe malegreyne and canel and datestones or of olyues and þis helpeþ muchel For to make fast þe teþe in þe heued and to do awey þe ache of hem 3if þat þei stenche noght Tak gallas v or v and mak hem smalle and seþe in strong eysil and kepe þis licour hote in þe mouþe twis or þis or more and þat þat is in þe beten do it in coton and lege to þe gomes and 3if þat it comeþ a doune to þe eres and þan tak castor and seþe in oyle and do in þe eres or elles tak musceleon and do it in a onyon þat is holgh or elles do it in a shelle of a neye and hete it and do it in þe or elles tak aloes and comune oyle and seþe hem to gyder and do in þe ere For to know 3if ache of þe heued comeþ of colryk and þes bien þe tokenynges þe eyen bien rede þei may noght slepe no þei may no3t loke a3eyn þe sone and þei suffren muche sownyng in þe eres For þis maladie tak aysil and meng wiþ oleum violaceum or elles wiþ oleum rosaceum and wete it in a lynnen cloute and lege to þe front and whan it is drie wete þe cloute anoþer tyme and lege anoþer tyme to þe front and þus do be feel tymes or elles tak populeon and tempre it wiþ oleum or elles wiþ oleum rosaceum or elles be þe iuse of þe nightshode A nobil medicine for sounyng of eres Tak þe sespounge and seþe it wiþ oleum violaceum or wiþ oleum rosaceum or wiþ wyne and do to þe ere A nobil medicine for greuous ache as it were in franesye Take þe iuse of smalache wiþ oleum violaceum or wiþ oleum rosaceum and do in þe ere or elles tak þe ius of þe maneras and do in þe nose A nobil medicine for þe posteme in þe bygynnyng of his wexyng and makeþ þat man may noght slepe Tak malewu violet and þe popie and seþe hem in water and þan do in þi fete and þe legges vp to þe knen and wassh hem welle and þan do shaue þe soles of þe fete wiþ a knyf and þan do enoynt hem wiþ popileon or elles wiþ oleum violaceum or elles wiþ oleum rosaceum Anoþer for ache and for sounyng of þe eres Take 3elkes of eyren and seþe hem in water and wreng oute þe water of hem and do it in þe eres Now it is to know whan þe fleumatik is mengyd wiþ þe colerik and comyng in to þe face and makeþ þare whelkes and 3if þat colrik ariseþ þe whelkes shalle beo rede and sharp and comeþ oute of hem as it were blode and 3if þat fleumatik ariseþ in þe same place þe whelkes bien nassh 3if tyme and elde after do 3if patriarcha and þan mak þis oynement Tak brent lede litarge and þan mastic aloes fraunkensens ceruce and draguncea and stamp and meng hem wiþ oleum rosaceum and wiþ þe iuse of stonhore and scer hem wel in a morter of bras and do dry and do to oyle Now 3if þat it beo þat it comeþ of þe fleumatyk and is in somer do 3if hym patriark or elles take þe rote of walwort and seþe it in water bote make clene þe rote of þe erþe þat is aboute it and þan whan it is wele ysoþe do streyne þorow a cloþe and do þe seek drenk fastyng Now 3if þat be flewmatik renne of blode þan do to þis oynement forsayd crowlek and smerewort And 3if þat þis sekenes comeþ in wynter do 3if þe seek jeralogodion ymengyd wiþ trifera And 3if þat it come of sangwyne þe whelkes shal be rede and somdel nassh And þis be in somer clense þe seek wiþ þe water þat maydenhere is seþe in and enoynt wiþ þe same oynement For swellyng of þe face þat comeþ of hete Take þe iuse of walwort wiþ oleum violaceum or wiþ oleum rosaceum and wete a lynnen cloute and lege to þe face And 3if þat it beo of wyne or pouder or be ony oþer auenture Tak mastik fraunkensens and aloes wiþ þe iuse of ribwort vntemperid and lege þer to For ache of þe eyen and suffren þer of gret anguyse as grauel wer in hem Tak þe iuse of paritorie wiþ white of a neye or elles aqua rosacea wiþ þe white of a neye and wassh ate morne and ate eue wiþ þe water þat roses is soþe in and 3if þat þe maladie haþe last long Take mastic aloes and frauncensens and stamp hem and tempre wiþ þe melk of a woman and tempre þes in þe maner of an oynement and enoynt þe eyen ate eue Now 3if þat it be þat grete hete be in þe eyen Tak reyne water and wassh þe forheued and þe eyen and 3if þat þer beo a grete brennyng do tak a lynnen cloute and wete it in womannes melk and do in þe eyen And 3if þat þe eyen bien moist of long tyme and grete swollen and þe eyebrowen also for þis swellyng do 3if hym oliban or elles opopira in þe daye or in þe day An oynement for þe same and do kepe Tak of gumme arabie mastic saunk de dragoun and of þe bark of malegrayne and þe popie and hennebanne be euen weght and mak poudre and tempre þes wiþ aqua rosacea and wiþ þe white of a neye and lege a brode wiþin a lynnen cloute and lege to þe front and for to kepe þis oynement Tak fressh rosen and do hem in a newe potte and do to hote water þat be scaldyng hote and couer þis potte and lete it stonde alle a neght in þis maner and þan do streyne þis þorow a streynour and þan do it in a noþer vessel þat it haue a streit hole and lege oyle aboue and kepe it Now 3if þat þere bien blak spotten in þe eyen and bien fressh in þe bygynnyng Do 3if hem opopira or diaolibanum or elles esdram and tempre aloes wiþ þe iuse of paritorie And 3if þat þei be olde be a moneþ or two do to þe pouder of sarcocolle or elles þe pouder of þe bone of sepie and 3if þat þer come oute ony filþ Do 3if jeralogodion and 3if þan anoþer opopiram and þan mak þis oynement Tak ceruse and þe flour of eris les þan of alle þe oþer and a litel of colofoyne and of mastik and of fraunkensens and a litel saunk de dragoune and tempre wiþ white wyne or elles wiþ oleum rosaceum For a sekenesse þat is in þe nose and it is yclepid polipus Tak apostolicon and mak a tent and do it in oleum rosaceum and þan take sarcocollum and þe flour þer of and make pouder and do þis pouder vpon þe tent and do in þe nose and þan lege þer vpon oxijocroceum Now it is touche of a maladie þat comeþ a doune to þe chekes and makeþ a gaderyng to gyder of þe synnewes in þe maner of þe cramp and may noght close þe eyen to gyder For þis maladye And þe bygynnyng do enoynt hym ate þe fure wiþ þis oynement aragon and þan do lete blode vnder þe tong For to make faire þe teþe and whyte Take þe bark of þe rote of lentisci and frote wele þe teþe þer wiþ Also take þe bark of þe grene notte and dry it and frote þe teþe For gomes þat bien fulle of blode Take þe bark of þe poumegarnette or elles balausicum and seþe hem in eysil and holde þis eysil in þe mouþe A nobil medicine for heres þat bien frette a way be þe morfew aboute a mannesbeerd for oþer while þe morfew doþe a wey a mannesberd For þis to make here wex Do ate þe bygynnyng shaue þe stede where þe heres bien fret awey and þan do frote so harde þe same place til þat þe blode come oute And þan tak þe biene þat þe founden dede in þe hony and mak poudre and þe pouder of tartari and meng hem to gyder and strew vpon þe bare place For þe squinincie Take þe pouder of percily and hony and do hem to gyder and do lete blode vnder þe tong and make a gorgete of þe pouder and of þe hony and a noþer of diameron and 3if þat it beo so þat þe voice be restrued do mak a stew in þis maner Tak hote coles and do hem in a sherd and do aboue þes coles a lytel licorice and mirre and storax and galbanum and botir and holde þe mouþe opyn ouer þe hole þat þe smoke may entre þer in For coldenesse of þe stomac and of þe brest Do enoynt þe seek wiþ diamarciaton or wiþ diasthea and do mak an emplastre of oxirocroceum and 3if þat it come of drenkyng of water þat be colde or of colde metes and be stoppyd wiþ in do lege vpon þe stomac oxirocroceum or apostolicon and do 3if hym among hote water ate morne and after mete do 3if diamargariton And 3if þat þer beo brennyng and þe heued ygreuyd and þe soles of feete and þe feete hote and whan he haþe ete ynogh sone þei kesteþ oute ate mouþe twis in þe wyke wiþ hote water And 3if wynd comeþ and make derkenesse in þe eyen do 3if electuarium dulce or elles diacimmium and 3if þe wynd comeþ adoune in to þe bowels do 3if electuarium dulce in þe same maner Now it is to touche of a sekenes þat is clepid dissinteria and bien two on is vpon þe nauelle and þe toþer is beneþen and anoþer is in þe stomac and 3if þat it beo in þe stomac he suffreþ muche þirst and grete ache in þe heued and 3if þat it be in þe bowels vpon þe nauelle he haþe grete tourmentyng and 3if þat it be beneþe he haþe grete ache in þe reynes and grete angyse of deliueraunce beneþe medicine for þis maladye of stomac do mak a sirup in þis maner Tak rosen and sank dragonne and do seþe hem in reyny water and þan do streyne and mak a sirup and do drenk wiþ water þat malew before in And 3if þat it be beneþe Tak þe iuse of plantayne and misse and bolum and stamp þes to gyder and seide alle þes to gyder in reyny water and þan do streyne alle þes and mak clisters and putte in and he shalle be delyuered An emplastre for þe maladye of þe brest and of þe reynes forsayd Take þe kyrnels of þe poume garnette and bren hem and euforbium gumme arabie bolum and mastic and saunk de dragoune and þe barc of þe poume garnette and stamp alle þes togyder and breng hem in to pouder þat it wonder smal pouder and tempre þis poudre wiþ þe iuse of plantayne and wiþ eysil and wiþ þe white of a ney and lege it in a lynnen clowte and do to þe brest and to þe reynes Now it is to touche þe sekenes of þe bowel wiþin þe body þat is iclepid þe lyuer þe whiche is sometyme hote of trauaile and oþerwhile of hote mete For þis maladie mak an emplastre and lege þer vpon and mak þis emplastre in þis maner Tak sandalum album and rubeum gumme of arabie and þe sede of roses and of purcelane and stamp hem to gyder and do to bere mele and þe iuse of þe nightshode or elles wiþ aqua rosacea and tempre and make þis hote ouer þe fure as water and take a cloþe and wete it þer in and lege it vpon þe syde or elles take þe iuse of þe nyghtshode And 3if þat þe lyuer be ache ifyd of þe splene Tak þe iuse of þe smal ache and of þe fenelsede and seþe alle þes to þe halfendel and do to suker or elles wiþ oute suker and 3if þe fastyng þat is seke ate morne and ate þe seek ete no mete or mydday Now 3if þat þis sekenesse falleþ in þe colryke and be long lastyng Do make þis water Take maydenhere and þe rote of borage and þe rote of paritorie and þe rote of hertestong and þe rotes forsayd do seþe hem to þe halfendel and þan do streyne þis licour and mak þe seek drenk ate morne sponful Now it is to touche 3if þat þe splen be yswolle Takex or of wormes þat bien in þe water þe whiche do souken oute þe blode of þe mannes leg and do put hem vpon þe splen and þat þei do abyde þer vpon til þat þei fallen þer from and þan do sone anone mak an emplastre of once or elles of oxirocroceo and 3if þat it may no3t be yfound þis emplastre þan Tak galbanum amoniac terebyntyne and mak hem hote ouer þe fure in eysil and þan do streyne þorow a cloþe and þan do boyle a lytel wyle and þan do þer to colophoyne and a litel of mele of faynegrec and meng hem to gyder and þan do þes in water and þan do mak nassh in þe maner of an emplastre and do oyle þer to and hete ate þe fure and lege it vpon a cloute A noþer emplastre for þe same Tak rosyne and wete it in water and melt it in hote water or in eysil is þe betir and þan do þer to mastic ypoudred and alitel of colofoyne and meng alle þes to gyder and do hem ouer þe fure and þan do water aboue and lege in þe same maner vpon þe splen And 3if þat it beo so þat þe man þat haþe þis sekenes and haþe þe wombe yswole be long tyme do 3if þe seek ieralagodion or elles theodoricon or elles euperisten and enoynt in bare welle wiþe diamarciaton or elles wiþ aragon and þan do hong hym vp be þe left arme

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/daniel_rosemary_converted.xml	s3	sethe þe flowrys in eurose  drynk it kold Also eyther of þe laste pociouns is mythti medicine to hem þat arn disposyd in tesyk  to seknesse of þe lwngys and of þe brest Also to hem þat han feble stomaks Also to hem þat arn seke on þe leuere  disposyd to þe dropesie Also to hem þat breden postemys on þe rybbys or on þe mydrede Also to hem þat repleyt wyth wykked homores in þe body Also þe last pocioun is a mythty medicyn to hem þat han mygreyn often tyme first þe hed waschen in þe same Also þe same pocioun causyth  genderyth good blod  gladyth þe herte  kepyth  sawyth þe body fro acuis Also þe same pocioun helpyth mythtely  counnfortyth aftyr blodlast  namely 3if on hawe bled ouer mykyl in what wyse it be Also ageyn cold  febilnesse of cerebre sethe þe erbe in wyn  clense it  drynke it hot  wasche the hed þer wyth  wrythe it wel Also 3if þou hawe gret cold in þin hed take þe smoke of his bark in þin nase  þou schalt felyn helpe Also 3if þou  been  feble  swete ouer meche wasche þin hed wyth water þat þe lewys arn sothyn in  it is auobyd thyng Also þe samen medycyn delyueryth fro þe cowhe Also take an hundred peper greynes  þer wyth þe jows of his flourys  his lewys  wyth a lytyll hony make ij pelotes  ete þe ton at morwyn  þe toþer at ewen and mythtely it delyueryth fro þe cowhe Also þe same doth his jows dronken Also chow his rote  it lessyth peyne in þe teth Also doth hys jows 3if þou helde yt well in þi mowth Also þe colys of hys stalkys bownden in a clene lynene clowt 3if þi teth ben well froten þerwyth it sleth wormys in þe teth  kepyth þe teth fro rotyng  fro ake  fro wormys Also watir þat his lewys arn sothyn in to þe myddys or to þe thredde del and þanne clense it  medele it wyth wyn  dronkyn  first mad soppys þer inne and it astoryth apetyt lost Also þe jows of hys braunchys  his lewys and flowrys medelyd wyth good old wyn  hot watyr  oftyn tyme dronken distroyeth þe skabbe Also his jows medelyd wyth hony  vinegre helyth hurtynggys of þe qwyte in þe eye 3if it be anoyntyd þer wyth Also his flowrys  his lewys stampyd helyn þe feber quarteyn 3if it be dronken aforn þe actes Also hys flowrys sothyn in red wyn fyn  cler  drynkke it cold aforn þe actes  it helpyth  helyth þe quarteyn Also vse rosmaryn in qwat wyse þat þou wyt  it sleth wermys in þe body and suffryth hem no3t to bredyn in þe body Also bully his rote in strong vinegre  wasche þi feet þerin and schwln is neuer fallyn owt of þe joynt Also ageyn inflaciouns in þe leggys  ake  pyne of þe gowte sethe hys lewys in water þanne wasche well þi leggys þer wyth þanne wappe þi leggys abowtyn wyth bombace  cotown  wyth erbe benet also sothyn in water and wyth þe forseyde sothen lewys leyd abowen in a clene wollyn clowt and it helpyth wonderly Also his lewys stampyd and leyd on þe cancre it sleth þe cancre Also þe erbe leyd at a dore catchyth awey alle maner venemys wormys thorow his odowr  suffryth hem now3t for to entryn Also 3if a man or a womman bere on hym a stalke or a staf þer of it kepyth hym fro thresse  fro wykked spritys as well be nyth as be day for kyndely it is contrarious to deuelys  to wikkyd spritys as þe ston þat is callyd Jet Also make a spon of hys tre an ete þerwyth  it is helply to the body ageyn venym  poysoun Also 3if on hyde hymself in a busch þer of or ellys he be wappyd weel in his lewys  his braunchys no thonder no leuene schall hym towchyn ne smytyn ne deren þe same doth þe lorer tre  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s2	Þe Secunde Boke The fyrst capytyl Capitulum i  of yougthe and browght vp with venym  þat þe natur of þat mayde was turnyd into þe natur of serpentis  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s4	And had I no3t ayouyn þe warnyng at þe fyrst tyme þat thow haddyst aloyne by her  þu hadist bene starke dede  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s10	Trost neuir in onwyse mennys seyingis  as þei þat seyne þat þe kunnyng of sterris is hard to be knowyn  and also þe cours of planetis  and þei sey þat no man may cum þerby  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s11	But sqwyche pepyl þei knowe no3t qwat þei sey  for to þe power of mannys vndyrstondyng þer is no thyng hard  for alle þingys be knowabyl in vey of resun  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s12	And odyr folys þer be also  þat sey þat God prouydid and ordeynyd fro þe beginnyng euirlastyng  qwerfor þei sey þat it profytith no3t to know before qwat schal betyde aftyrward  sythyn it is so þat it is necessary þei schuld falle and must nedys be  qwat is wurth þan þe kunnyng of sterris  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s24	It owyth to be knowyn þat astronomy is dyuydid in to þre partis  þat is to sey in þe ordynacion of þe heuynnis and of þe speeris and þe dysposycion of planetis  and þe dyuision of þe sygnys  þe elongacion also of hem  and of þe maner of þer werkynkys  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s25	And þis parte of astronomy is clepyd þe syens  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s26	The secunde parte is of þe qwalyte and þe maner of knowyng þe meuyng of þe fyrmament  þe rysyng or þe spryngyng of þe sygnys  vppon thyngis neghyng þe celestyal speris or euir þei come to knowlech be vysual appeirryng  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s27	And þis is þe secunde parte of astronomye  or þe konnyng of domys  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s31	For þe kepyng of helth is bettir than ony medycine  and þis doctrine and þise secretis be ryght necessari to þe gouernanz of þis world  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s63	And þei þat be of cold natur  þo thyngis þat be cold in temperauns acorde to þe norchyng of þat dysposicion  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s72	And if þis febylnes and indygest mater be habundaunt  þer comyth þerof streykyng owte of þe armys and þe body  and þe bak bowyth  and þe nek  and many odyr thyngis besyde þat be contrarius to helth  destroyus of þe body  and coruptifis of natur  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s77	For þe strecchyng owte of þi membris strenghyt alle þi body  and makyth dygest humoris ascende and to fylle alle partys  and þe kembyng of þine hede bryngyth owte vaporys and fumys of noyus humorys  þe qwyche in tyme of slepyng ascendyd fro þe stomak to þe hed  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s83	It opynnyth þe stoppyngis of þe brayne  it makyth fulle and fleschy þe nek and þe armys  it claryfiyth þe face and þe syght  it strenghyth þe wytte  and it slowyth and make age to tary  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s85	For þe spyrite is no3t refrescyd but only be delytesum tast  and alle sqwete odyris is hys mete  and þe spyrite is made stronge and refreschyd and opynnyd  þe body is confortyd  þe herte joyth  and þe blode þanne begynnyth to renne into þe veynys  of gladnes of þe spyrite  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s89	 But conceyue þat in þo dayis Crystyn feyth was no3t  qwerfor he remembryth no3t of þe seruyse of God  þat men schuld fyrst serue God  and aftyr do þat qwyche is conseruyng of helth of þe body   
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s90	Þe eght capitil Capitulum Qwan þe owr is comyn and þi appetyte forte ete  aftyr þine vse and custum  vse a lytyl labour beforn  owdyr in rydyng or walkyng or sqwyche anodyr werk doying  for þat helpyth myche þe body  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s93	But ordyr aftyr nortur and aftyr þe gyse of seruyse þine etyng  so þat þu begynne no3t atte last cours and aftyr retorne to þe fyrst  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s94	But if þu wult kepe þe to o cours fede on þe last in þe begynnyng and retorn no3t  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s95	Allso to þe helth of þi body haue consyderacion  settyng one beforn anodyr of þi metys  as þus  if þu take at þi mele a potage  þat þe kende þerof be forto lose þi wombe  and aftyr þat anodyr potage of qwych þe kend is to make constipat  if þe molyficatyf go beforn  it makyth lyght and esy digestion and eke egestyon  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s96	And if þe constipatyf potage be etyn first  and aftir þat þe molyficatyf  þei be consumyd both with effecte of losyng  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s97	And if it be so þat a man take many sondry potagis or metys qwyche be lyte of dygestyon  it behouyth þat somme mete be etyn beforn þo  þe qwyche is substancial of abydyng  þat it make resydens in þe bottom of þe stomak  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s98	For þe deppest part of þe stomak is most myghty for to dygest  for as myche as þer be in þe bottum fleschly partis  and also þat it is ner þe lyuir  of qwyche hete of þe lyuir alle metis be chefly dygestyd  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s102	The nynghe capitil her beginnith Capitulum And qwan it is so þat þu hast etyn  walke softly a thousand pacys  or ellis stonde ryght vppe  þat þe mete may descend fully to þe bottum of þi stomak fully  þan vppon a soft bed ley þe to slepe  and rest one hour vppon þi bedde on þi ryght syde  and þan torne þe on þi left syde and fulfylle þe resydw of þi slepe on þat syde  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s106	And þe remedy is þat anone þu drynke a byttir syrippe as is centory þe siruppe  and þe syruppe of wurmewode  and sqwyche odyr  with a cold watyr  as is endyue  borage  and sqwyche odyr  and be þis mene to prouoke a vomyte  for þat enprisonnyng of mete in þe stomak is vtter destruccion to þe body  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s108	Than bewar þat þu slepe no3t beforn mete  for þat wul drye þe and make þi body and þi face leene and owte of lykyng  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s109	And aftir mete it dothe euyn þe contrary  makyng þe stronge  and nurchyth þe and makyth þe in lykyng  for qwyll þat a man slepyth  þe naturalle hete dyffusely rennyth fro alle partys to þe stomak and to þe iner partis of þe stomak  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s110	And þan is þe stomak made stronge to seeth þe mete þat is withinne  for þan þe vertu racional sekyth reste  and alle þe spyritis be in qwyete  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s111	Qwerfor sum fylisofris sey þat þe sopir profytith mor þat is etyn at euyn  þan þat mele þat is etyn at mydday  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s113	But atte þe euyn sopir is alle þe contrary  if it be so a man hath no3t etyn to myche at none

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s120	And bewar in specyal þat þu ete neuir tyl þat þu knowe surly þat þi mete qwych þu etyst beforn be ful dygest  and þat þi stomak be voyde  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s123	And if he ete qwan þat he hath goode appetyte  he schale fynde þe hete of þe stomak as a brennyng fyre  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s124	And as sone as euir thow hast dysir to ete  þu schuldyst ete anone  for but þu ete sone at þat tyme þe stomac is anone repleschyd with noyus and euyl humoris  þe qwych it drawyth to yt fro alle þe body of superfluyteis  qwyche werkyng trowbyllyth þe brayn  sendyng vppe euyl vaporis to þe hede  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s128	Ver begynnyth qwan þe sonne entryth þe sygne of Aryes

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s169	On wyse be deth natural þat no man may scape  þat qwan very age comyth  þe qwyche is cold and drye  þe body is destroyd

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s186	And he þat refusith þis medicyne may falle into perlyus sekenes  þat is to sey  sekenes of þe eyn  sekenes of þe brayn  and odyr many  fro qwyche God kepe þe  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s187	Þe eghtene capitil Capitulum The breste is þe secunde part of þe body  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s188	And if in þis parte þer be foundyn superfluyteis  þei be knowyn be þise tokynnis  þe tonge is heuy  þe mowth is salt  and in þe mowth of þe stomak þe mete þat is etyn sauiryth byttyr  and with þat a dysposicion to þe koughe  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s191	Þe nyntene capitil Capitulum The eyn be þe thyrd part of þe body  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s194	And þo thyngis þat confort þe syght and þe eyn be kendis goode confortatif  and þe watyr or þe juse of fynkel  of verueyn  of rosis  of celydony  of rwe  and oftyn  þe eyn opyn  to dyppe hem oftyn in cold watyr and to loke on þe watyr  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s199	Also þe hede fulle of wynde stofyth þise materis into þe eyn  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s201	Than febylnes is knowyn besyde þise  þat if þe fygur of þe eye  qwyche schuld be rownd in þe cyrcuite  if it fayle þat  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s202	And þe werkyng of natur of þe eyn be knowyn be þis dysposicion  tho eyn þat meve fast be of hote natur  late of meuyng  colde  þei þat be ful of humoris  and qwan þei lawghe  ful of watyr  þei be moyst  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s205	Thei þat may se nye and no3t ferre  þei haue a cler and vysibil spyrite of syghte  but it is smal  for qwyche smalnes þei be impotent to se aferr  
./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s206	Thei þat may se fer and no3t ner  þei haue a myghti and myche of þe spyrite of syghte and of vysual vertu  þe qwych is grose  moyst  and perturbate  qwerfor  or þe syght may haue very knowlech of þat þing  it nedyth gret dystauns to depur it  þat þe grose vapowris be departyd fro hem

./data/MIDDLE-MODERN-ENGLISH-MEDICAL-CORPUS-Copy/01_MEMT_Texts/de_caritate_the_priuyte_of_priuyteis_converted.xml	s385	And if þe sunne and þe mone be in a flewmatyk sygne  þe laxatyfe þat is youyn warkyth esyly  and namely if þe mone be in waxyng  for as Doctour Plynyus seyth þat  þe moone waxyng  alle humorys þat be in a man encrese  and also  decresyng þe mone  humoris mynwse or decrese  experyens schewyth
